Hi, Jarod.

As Jarod Kientz wrote to Dr. Math
On 09/22/2004 at 18:12:18 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>Is an number divided by zero consider to be a "real number" or 
>an "imaginary number", or is it neither?
>
>[Difficulty]
>I don't know if you get infinity when you divide a number by zero or 
>not. Let alone what it's classified as.
>
>[Thoughts]
>x/0=?

Neither; it's not a number at all. See our FAQ:

  Dividing by 0
  http://mathforum.org/dr.math/faq/faq.divideby0.html

People often say informally that 1/0 is "infinity", but as you'll see,
that's not really valid.

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


- Doctor Peterson, The Math Forum
